definitions.definition: To represent (a concept , theme , or principle ) by an instance .
examples: To see and test the result of one's CSS for any particular HTML element, one must instantiate that element in a document.

definitions.definition: To create an object (an instance) of a specific class .
examples: To instantiate a class, we call its constructor.

main_definition: ( transitive ) To represent (a concept , theme , or principle ) by an instance . [from 20th c.]
secondary_definitions: ( transitive , object-oriented programming ) To create an object (an instance) of a specific class . [from 20th c.]
